<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>50 ways -- OK, 10 -- to leave your @#%$</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
By Robert Philpot<br>
Star-Telegram Staff Writer<br>
<br>
ASSOCIATED PRESS ARCHIVES<br>
<br>
These days, it just wouldn't be a sweeps month without a Michael Jackson special -- or six. Fortunately, so far, only one has been scheduled: Michael Jackson's Private Home Movies, which airs tonight on, where else, Fox.<br>
<br>
In what has become something of a mantra for TV critics this season, let me just say, enough already. Really, the guy sang Leave Me Alone in the '80s, but how can we leave him alone if he won't say goodbye? Here's one way. Or make that 10 ways, to avoid watching the gloved one tonight:<br>
<br>
1. Go to the Main St. Fort Worth Arts Festival, which starts today. Thursday is usually the least-crowded day of the four-day fest in downtown. Turn to Page 3 for more details.<br>
<br>
2. Go see the Fabulous Thunderbirds at the Canyon Club inside Dallas' Bronco Bowl and ask them what the heck they're doing there when they belong at the Main St. fest.<br>
<br>
3. If you must have your Michael fix, dust off that old vinyl copy of Thriller -- or better yet, play your CD, where you can skip The Girl Is Mine, or at least fast-forward through that part where Paul McCartney and Jackson start talking to each other.<br>
<br>
4. Watch Sabrina (Melissa Joan Hart) get married on Sabrina, the Teenage Witch) (7 tonight, KDAF/Channel 33). It will be your last chance to see a new Sabrina, and since the show's been on for seven seasons, shouldn't you watch it at least once?<br>
<br>
5. Check out a historic Friends that, for the first time in the long history of the New York-set show, provides a significant role for an African-American (Aisha Tyler).<br>
<br>
6. Go to the USA Film Festival at the Angelika Film Center in Dallas, where you can see the local premiere of I'll Be There or Raising Victor Vargas. I'll Be There was written and directed by star Craig Ferguson of The Drew Carey Show. Ferguson will be there, so you'll still have a TV connection!<br>
<br>
7. Rent the DVD Standing in the Shadows of Motown, about the session musicians who were the unsung heroes of the classic soul music of the '60s and '70s. They'll make you forget all about Michael.<br>
<br>
8. If you really just have to have someone self-promoting in your life, buy Madonna's new American Life CD and listen to it while watching her appearance tonight on Will &amp; Grace (8:05 p.m., KXAS/Channel 5) with the sound off.<br>
<br>
9. Survivor: The Amazon is one of the best Survivors yet, and it's not too late to catch up with it (7 tonight, KTVT/Channel 11).<br>
<br>
10. Watch Jackson's ex, Lisa Marie Presley, express herself on a half-hour show at 8 p.m. on VH1. And if you stick around on VH1 -- even more Madonna! There's a repeat of her Madonna Speaks special at 8:30.<br>
